The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) has confirmed the death of three more persons who were in the three-storey building which collapsed on Ibadan Street, in the Ebute Metta, Lagos State on Sunday night. Recall that NEMA confirmed the death of five persons, with 23 persons including children rescued alive. NEMA’s acting coordinator, Ibrahim Farinloye, in a statement on Monday, confirmed the death of three men, expressing that the recovered bodies were taken to the mortuary. “Two male additional bodies recovered, making eight deaths,” Farinloye said. A search and rescue operation is ongoing by NEMA, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, Lagos State Fire and Rescue Services, and others. However, the number of people trapped is still uncertain.